<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CD9CBD8FDEB1FF4D" bold="true" box="[475,502,159,183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="33AC23CD266EFFE5CDB2BD8FDC48FF4D" authorityName="Brade" authorityYear="1939" box="[501,783,159,183]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pygmaeorchis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CDB2BD8FDC48FF4D" box="[501,783,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Pygmaeorchis brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known only from the high elevation mountain areas around 
<collectingRegion id="366896AC266EFFE5CD53BDD3DEECFF21" box="[276,427,195,219]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(mislabeled 
<collectingRegion id="366896AC266EFFE5CE74BDD3DD86FF21" box="[563,705,195,219]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
on the specimen 
<typeStatus id="2B17E6EC266EFFE5CF31BDD3DCEFFF21" box="[886,936,195,219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">type</typeStatus>
). There, it was reported to grow as an epiphyte in the rainforest at ~ 
<quantity id="3354F5AB266EFFE5CD04BDF7DED2FF05" box="[323,405,231,255]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
in elevation (
<bibRefCitation id="903D25BF266EFFE5CE62BDF7DDB2FF05" author="van den Berg, C. &amp; Pridgeon, A. M. &amp; Cribb, P. J. &amp; Chase, M. C. &amp; Rasmussen, F. N." box="[549,757,231,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="2006" refId="ref1810" refString="van den Berg, C. (2006) Pygmaeorchis. In: Pridgeon, A. M., Cribb, P. J., Chase, M. C. &amp; Rasmussen, F. N. (2006) Epidendroideae (Part One). Genera Orchidacearum. Vol. 4. Oxford University Press, New York, pp. 303 - 305." type="book chapter" year="2006">van den Berg 2006</bibRefCitation>
). The new record confirms the presence of this rare species in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="366896AC266EFFE5CC9CBC1BDE2DFED9" box="[219,362,267,291]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="6C9744CB266EFFE5CD3FBC1BDEF1FED9" box="[376,438,267,291]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="0.[136,229,1999,2021]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1066,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-306@0.[151,1436,1066,1974]" captionTargetPageId="0" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of the species of Pygmaeorchis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423750/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="33AC23CD266EFFE5CD8BBC1BDDA3FED9" authorityName="Brade" authorityYear="1939" box="[460,740,267,291]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pygmaeorchis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CD8BBC1BDDA3FED9" box="[460,740,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Pygmaeorchis brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found growing epiphytically on 
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5C828BC1BDB84FED9" box="[1135,1219,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">candeia</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="33AC23CD266EFFE5C895BC1BDE4CFEBD" authority="Lessing (1829: 317)" authorityName="Lessing" authorityPageNumber="317" authorityYear="1829" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Eremanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5C895BC1BDA15FED9" box="[1234,1362,267,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Eremanthus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="903D25BF266EFFE5C91FBC1BDE4CFEBD" author="Lessing, F." pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="240 - 356" refId="ref1574" refString="Lessing, F. (1829) De Synanthereis Herbarii Regii Berolinensis dissertatio prima. Linnaea 4: 240 - 356." type="journal article" year="1829">Lessing (1829: 317)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="33AC23CD266EFFE5CD5FBC3FDEC8FEBD" box="[280,399,303,327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) in a cloud forest at an elevation of 
<quantity id="3354F5AB266EFFE5CF6BBC3FDCC4FEBD" box="[812,899,303,327]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.56" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" unit="m" value="1560.0">1560 m</quantity>
. It co-occurs with 
<taxonomicName id="33AC23CD266EFFE5C811BC20DE3CFE91" authority="Barbosa Rodrigues (1881: 112)" authorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" authorityPageNumber="112" authorityYear="1881" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Octomeria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptophylla">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5C811BC20DA0DFEBD" box="[1110,1354,303,327]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Octomeria leptophylla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="903D25BF266EFFE5C913BC3FDE3CFE91" author="Barbosa Rodrigues, J." pageId="3" pageNumber="300" refId="ref1415" refString="Barbosa Rodrigues, J. (1881) Octomeria leptophylla. In: Barbosa Rodrigues, J., Genera et species orchidearum novarum quas collecgit, descripsit et iconibus illustravit, vol. 2. C. et H. Fleiuss, Rio de Janeiro, 112 pp." type="book" year="1881">Barbosa Rodrigues (1881: 112)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is also a rare species (
<bibRefCitation id="903D25BF266EFFE5CEF2BC43DB66FE91" author="Menini Neto, L. &amp; Docha Neto, A." box="[693,1057,339,363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="461 - 465" refId="ref1596" refString="Menini Neto, L. &amp; Docha Neto, A. (2009) Redescoberta e tipificacao de Octomeria leptophylla Barb. Rodr. (Orchidaceae), micro-orquidea endemica de Minas Gerais, Brasil. Rodriguesia 60: 461 - 465. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860200960216" type="journal article" year="2009">Menini Neto &amp; Docha Neto 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F413584E266EFFE5CCFABC67DCD1FE75" blockId="3.[136,1452,159,690]" box="[189,918,375,399]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CCFABC67DE73FE75" bold="true" box="[189,308,375,399]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Phenology</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CD7CBC67DE11FE75" bold="true" box="[315,342,375,399]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">—</emphasis>
Flowering was recorded in September and November.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F413584E266EFFE5CCFABC8BDBA3FD9D" blockId="3.[136,1452,159,690]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CCFABC8BDEE7FE49" bold="true" box="[189,416,411,435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Conservation status</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CDE0BC8BDE85FE49" bold="true" box="[423,450,411,435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="33AC23CD266EFFE5CD85BC8BDD9BFE49" authorityName="Brade" authorityYear="1939" box="[450,732,411,435]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pygmaeorchis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5CD85BC8BDD9BFE49" box="[450,732,411,435]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Pygmaeorchis brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered as Data Deficient (DD) according to the criteria of IUCN (2017) in The Red Book on the Flora Endemic to the State of 
<collectingRegion id="366896AC266EFFE5CF35BCAFDB49FE2D" box="[882,1038,447,471]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="903D25BF266EFFE5C85BBCAFDA61FE2D" author="Menini Neto, L. &amp; Moulton, L. &amp; Moraes, M. &amp; Meneguzzo, T. &amp; Messina, T. &amp; Santos Filho, L. &amp; Negrao, R. &amp; Wimmer, F. &amp; Avancini, R. &amp; Novaes, L. &amp; Margon, H. &amp; Braga, R." box="[1052,1318,447,471]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="365 - 376" refId="ref1651" refString="Menini Neto, L., Moulton, L., Moraes, M., Meneguzzo, T., Messina, T., Santos Filho, L., Negrao, R., Wimmer, F., Avancini, R., Novaes, L., Margon, H. &amp; Braga, R. (2018) Orchidaceae. In: Martinelli, G., Martins, E., Moraes, M., Loyola, R. &amp; Amaro, R. (Orgs.) Livro vermelho da flora endemica do estado do Rio de Janeiro. Secretaria de Estado do Ambiente, Rio de Janeiro, pp. 365 - 376." type="book chapter" year="2018">
Menini Neto 
<emphasis id="C6D8845C266EFFE5C8E9BCD0DBA2FE2D" box="[1198,1253,447,471]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Only three records are currently known (including this one), representing an Extension of Occurrence (EOO) of approximately 
<quantity id="3354F5AB266EFFE5C928BCF3DFEDFDD8" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.226" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" unit="km" value="7226.0">7,226 km</quantity>
² and an Area of Occupation (AOO) of 
<quantity id="3354F5AB266EFFE5CE11BF17DDDAFDD8" box="[598,669,519,546]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
². Based on the current information and considering the criteria of 
<bibRefCitation id="903D25BF266EFFE5C92DBF17DF88FDB9" author="IUCN" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" refId="ref1525" refString="IUCN (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (acessed 23 March 2021)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
we classify it as Endangered: EN, B2a,b(ii,iii,iv,v). However, this is a tiny epiphytic species that is likely to pass unnoticed, further searching efforts may reveal its presence in neighboring areas with similar vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
